Specific Details: Making Heart Failure a public policy priority
DPOs Lobbied: Seán Kyne|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mairead McGuinness|MEP|European Parliament
Subject Matter: Making Heart Failure a public policy priority
Intended Results: Making Heart Failure a public policy priority::Support for the Heart Failure Declaration in the EU parliament
Lobbying Activities: November 2016 (Galway) Launch of the Ireland Heart Failure Barometer report by Minister Kyne.  A new Irish policy report on Heart Failure in Ireland.  The report was written by the Health Policy Partnership.  Also contributing to the content of the report were: cardiologists, people with heart failure, heart failure Clinical Nurse Specialists and general practitioners.  With input from the Heartbeat Trust and Croi, supported by Novartis.  Report recommendations: 1) Explicitly mention HF within existing chronic disease policies and ensure there are sufficient resources to implement the National Clinical Program for HF 2) Ensure that patients with symptoms of HF are diagnosed earlier and without delay 3) Create a coordinated national program linking hospital and community care 4) Support a national HF prevention program|Meeting|1::Support for heart failure at a European level (HF Declaration at the EU parliament).  Attend the launch of the HF Declaration at the EU parliament.|Meeting|1

Specific Details: Invitation to the launch of the ‘Galway Wind Park Sustainability Impact Report’ at SSE Red Oak, South County Business Park, on November 28th 2016. The 169MW project is being jointly delivered by SSE and Coillte, and is the largest of its kind currently under construction in Ireland. When completed in 2017, Galway Wind Park will be the country’s largest onshore wind farm, contributing significantly to Ireland’s 2020 40% renewable electricity target.
